00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,460
Let me introduce you.

289
00:15:46,540 --> 00:15:47,140
Ling Yikai.

290
00:15:49,260 --> 00:15:50,540
Zhao Lanxin mentions you a lot.

291
00:15:50,820 --> 00:15:51,500
We finally meet.

292
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:01,260
How are things?

293
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:03,420
Settling in okay?

294
00:16:04,900 --> 00:16:05,700
Not really.

295
00:16:05,980 --> 00:16:06,540
It's too big.

296
00:16:08,060 --> 00:16:08,980
You really bring

297
00:16:08,980 --> 00:16:10,340
that gaming vibe everywhere you go.

298
00:16:12,460 --> 00:16:14,140
We'll all be colleagues from now on.

299
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:15,940
I figured you two should meet.

300
00:16:17,180 --> 00:16:18,540
The company is paying

301
00:16:18,860 --> 00:16:20,300
the rent for this house you're in.

302
00:16:20,860 --> 00:16:22,820
That means the daily value you create

303
00:16:22,820 --> 00:16:24,660
can't be less than the rent.

304
00:16:26,140 --> 00:16:27,220
I'm not good at math.

305
00:16:28,420 --> 00:16:29,780
Isn't that your job?

306
00:16:30,580 --> 00:16:31,580
Let me make it simple.

307
00:16:32,420 --> 00:16:33,580
We'll soon announce

308
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:35,380
that Sansan is your other pen name.

309
00:16:36,420 --> 00:16:38,180
You wrote the top two

310
00:16:38,180 --> 00:16:38,900
most-read works.

311
00:16:39,422 --> 00:16:40,940
This will take you to the next level.

312
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:43,060
Your job is simple,

313
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:44,340
yet difficult.

314
00:16:45,660 --> 00:16:47,180
Just maintain your current standard.

315
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:48,860
As for the stats,

316
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:50,700
they can only go up.

317
00:16:51,460 --> 00:16:52,940
It's easier to conquer than defend.

318
00:16:53,740 --> 00:16:54,420
Not to mention,

319
00:16:54,620 --> 00:16:55,940
you have to hold two titles here.

320
00:16:58,380 --> 00:16:59,660
And if the views drop?

321
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:03,060
Seems you don't know Zhao Lanxin well.

322
00:17:04,180 --> 00:17:05,500
The moment your views drop,

323
00:17:06,060 --> 00:17:07,540
you'll be moving out of here.

324
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:18,888
Is that so?

325
00:17:20,460 --> 00:17:21,900
There's no free lunch.

326
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:23,940
You earned everything you have

327
00:17:24,340 --> 00:17:25,460
right now.

328
00:17:26,580 --> 00:17:27,860
Writers inevitably have

329
00:17:28,340 --> 00:17:29,580
their ups and downs.

330
00:17:31,260 --> 00:17:33,260
Zhao Lanxin doesn't have
the patience to wait.

331
00:17:34,140 --> 00:17:35,660
She'll just pivot to other writers

332
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:37,380
who can bring her more profit.

333
00:17:41,820 --> 00:17:43,300
It's not just this house, of course.

334
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,420
Your friends

335
00:17:45,820 --> 00:17:48,780
are currently expanding
an esports arena.

336
00:17:49,244 --> 00:17:50,755
It used to be an internet cafe.

337
00:17:52,860 --> 00:17:54,380
I don't know if they told you,

338
00:17:55,466 --> 00:17:56,740
but we signed an agreement.

339
00:17:57,711 --> 00:17:59,580
The expansion funds
from Colorful Culture Media

340
00:17:59,580 --> 00:18:00,580
count as an equity stake.

341
00:18:00,980 --> 00:18:02,700
You guys still run the daily operations.

342
00:18:03,420 --> 00:18:04,660
Nothing will change.

343
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:06,980
But if you choose

344
00:18:06,980 --> 00:18:08,020
not to work with us,

345
00:18:08,780 --> 00:18:10,420
I can't guarantee your friends

346
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:12,100
can keep this arena open.

347
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:14,660
What do you want?

348
00:18:24,300 --> 00:18:26,140
We can wait for you until...

349
00:18:30,180 --> 00:18:30,660
tomorrow.

350
00:18:44,900 --> 00:18:48,580
(Exclusive Licensing Contract: Gu Yan)

351
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:53,820
I was thinking

352
00:18:54,220 --> 00:18:54,940
we could consider

353
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:57,380
making the mysterious A'kong
the ultimate villain.

354
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:59,220
Any thoughts on this?

355
00:18:59,580 --> 00:19:00,100
Yes, Ms. Lin.

356
00:19:00,220 --> 00:19:01,140
I had the same thought.

357
00:19:01,800 --> 00:19:04,140
I can use a secret identity trope
to hook the readers.

358
00:19:04,311 --> 00:19:06,380
The plan was for A'kong
to oppose the female lead

359
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:07,740
the moment he appeared.

360
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,030
(Character Relationship Chart)
But actually,

361
00:19:09,044 --> 00:19:10,500
we can give A'kong an alter ego,

362
00:19:10,600 --> 00:19:11,777
put him beside the heroine,

363
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:12,866
and let him play dumb.

364
00:19:13,444 --> 00:19:14,610
Introducing a new character

365
00:19:14,610 --> 00:19:15,860
at such a critical juncture

366
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:17,260
is a bit risky.

367
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:19,620
So, if we do this,

368
00:19:19,780 --> 00:19:20,980
we need to write it in a way

369
00:19:21,500 --> 00:19:23,300
that gives the readers
an omniscient view.

370
00:19:23,460 --> 00:19:25,800
Make them feel like
two masterminds are about to clash.

371
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:26,500
That way,

372
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:27,700
long-time readers won't have

373
00:19:27,980 --> 00:19:29,100
their momentum broken.

374
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:30,755
Then, we introduce A'kong.

375
00:19:31,060 --> 00:19:31,460
Exactly.

376
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:32,700
This way,

377
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:34,940
A'kong's identity
becomes even more crucial.

378
00:19:35,380 --> 00:19:37,620
Everyone's entry point
into the web novel industry

379
00:19:37,620 --> 00:19:38,420
is different.

380
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:40,660
There might not
be much common ground there.

381
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,060
And the process varies, too.

382
00:19:42,220 --> 00:19:44,220
Some have smooth sailing
right from the start.

383
00:19:44,230 --> 00:19:46,010
For others,
the hardest part is getting started.

384
00:19:46,020 --> 00:19:46,740
Can't help that.

385
00:19:47,420 --> 00:19:48,340
But I feel like

386
00:19:48,660 --> 00:19:50,220
the total amount of hardship

387
00:19:50,460 --> 00:19:51,700
is probably about the same.

388
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:41,140
Tired?

389
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:45,820
I'm alright.

390
00:20:46,244 --> 00:20:47,180
You've worked hard.

391
00:20:47,940 --> 00:20:48,420
Not at all.

392
00:20:49,060 --> 00:20:49,780
I feel great.

393
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:52,420
Not a single day here feels wasted.

394
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:56,820
Finish what you're working on.

395
00:20:56,820 --> 00:20:57,540
Send it to me.

396
00:20:58,260 --> 00:20:58,780
This has

397
00:20:59,020 --> 00:21:00,780
my edits and notes for the last section.

398
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:02,780
If you have time today,

399
00:21:02,866 --> 00:21:04,620
finish it
and hand it over for formatting.

400
00:21:04,780 --> 00:21:06,000
Send it in tomorrow morning.

401
00:21:06,420 --> 00:21:06,780
Okay.

402
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:09,620
I'll go make you a cup of coffee.

403
00:21:10,180 --> 00:21:10,620
Thanks.

404
00:21:27,444 --> 00:21:28,860
"Order of the Mountain Ghost".

405
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:30,340
I read the novel.

406
00:21:30,340 --> 00:21:31,860
I don't think it's a smart choice.

407
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:33,260
He's no Gu Yan.

408
00:21:33,380 --> 00:21:34,380
Not even close.

409
00:21:34,390 --> 00:21:35,540
"Order of the Mountain Ghost"

410
00:21:35,540 --> 00:21:36,860
isn't a marketable concept.

411
00:21:37,020 --> 00:21:37,980
You're pouring

412
00:21:37,980 --> 00:21:39,700
so much effort and money into this.

413
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:42,222
If it bombs, it'll be a massive blow
to Chenxing and you.

414
00:22:06,380 --> 00:22:08,620
That's it for today's episode.

415
00:22:09,060 --> 00:22:11,820
I've prepared over ten episodes anyway.

416
00:22:11,888 --> 00:22:13,100
They are all different lengths.

417
00:22:13,288 --> 00:22:15,220
If there's not much to say,
I'll keep it short.

418
00:22:15,380 --> 00:22:16,700
If there's a lot to share,

419
00:22:16,700 --> 00:22:17,660
I'll talk a bit longer.

420
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,100
But the price is the same.

421
00:22:19,300 --> 00:22:20,420
No refund if it's short,

422
00:22:20,420 --> 00:22:21,670
and no extra fees if it's long.

423
00:22:21,688 --> 00:22:22,580
It's all about trust.

424
00:22:23,420 --> 00:22:24,420
Alright, that's all.

425
00:22:24,577 --> 00:22:25,577
Good night, everyone.

426
00:23:10,940 --> 00:23:12,140
(All edited. Looks okay to me.)

427
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:15,900
(If you think it's fine too,
the file is in your inbox. Just forward it.)

428
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:17,220
(From Your Lifesaver)

429
00:23:35,900 --> 00:23:36,780
When did you get here?

430
00:23:38,688 --> 00:23:39,888
Where's Prefrontal Cortex?

431
00:23:39,940 --> 00:23:40,740
He left with you?

432
00:23:42,700 --> 00:23:47,980
(Three Hours Earlier)

433
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:26,300
Prefrontal Cortex, right?

434
00:24:27,380 --> 00:24:28,620
Mr. He Han.

435
00:24:29,060 --> 00:24:29,780
Why are you here?

436
00:24:29,860 --> 00:24:30,300
Sit down.

437
00:24:31,740 --> 00:24:32,420
Where are you at?

438
00:24:32,688 --> 00:24:35,244
Has the mysterious one
for the first climax appeared?

439
00:24:35,460 --> 00:24:35,740
Yes.

440
00:24:36,260 --> 00:24:36,980
Almost.

441
00:24:38,140 --> 00:24:39,580
Mr. He Han, does this mean

442
00:24:39,740 --> 00:24:40,900
you've read my novel too?

443
00:24:42,020 --> 00:24:42,860
Very carefully.

444
00:24:43,540 --> 00:24:43,940
Thank you.

445
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:46,700
Thank you for your valuable feedback.

446
00:24:47,700 --> 00:24:48,020
Right.

447
00:24:48,688 --> 00:24:50,755
These are
the first ten chapters I finished.

448
00:24:51,133 --> 00:24:52,490
Based on Zhanqiao's suggestions,

449
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:53,911
I'll finish editing them tonight.

450
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:56,820
And, these
are the latest three chapters.

451
00:24:57,422 --> 00:24:59,088
We'll review them when she gets back.

452
00:24:59,340 --> 00:25:00,740
Let me see the first few chapters.

453
00:25:01,244 --> 00:25:02,620
I'll edit the last three for you.

454
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:05,900
You'll edit them for me?

455
00:25:07,220 --> 00:25:07,620
This...

456
00:25:08,340 --> 00:25:09,660
Isn't this inappropriate?

457
00:25:10,180 --> 00:25:10,940
Oh my.

458
00:25:11,820 --> 00:25:13,580
This is such a surprise.

459
00:25:14,700 --> 00:25:15,580
So what can I do?

460
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,060
Does Zhanqiao know?

461
00:25:17,180 --> 00:25:17,740
I'll get her.

462
00:25:17,740 --> 00:25:18,300
No, no, no.

463
00:25:18,333 --> 00:25:19,340
She knows everything.

464
00:25:19,460 --> 00:25:20,540
She asked me to help.

465
00:25:21,777 --> 00:25:23,044
Thank you, Mr. He.

466
00:25:23,666 --> 00:25:24,500
Thank you, Mr. He.

467
00:25:27,900 --> 00:25:28,740
Hurry up and write.

468
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:29,820
Right away.

469
00:25:30,733 --> 00:25:31,700
I'm just so excited.

470
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:48,540
♪I watch the stars in my eyes♪

471
00:25:48,860 --> 00:25:51,660
♪Slowly drift away♪

472
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:52,340
These parts

473
00:25:52,577 --> 00:25:53,300
are the same.

474
00:25:53,580 --> 00:25:56,220
♪Died a little inside last night♪

475
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:59,580
♪Cause I'll never see you again♪

476
00:26:01,340 --> 00:26:04,500
♪I'm waking up to silence around me♪

477
00:26:05,020 --> 00:26:07,780
♪Heal, can I heal?♪

478
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:12,420
♪All I want is nothing more♪

479
00:26:12,540 --> 00:26:15,980
♪Than to see your face someday♪

480
00:26:16,580 --> 00:26:17,660
♪We were lovers♪

481
00:26:17,660 --> 00:26:20,220
♪Till that very day♪

482
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:21,820
♪I'll remember♪

483
00:26:21,820 --> 00:26:23,940
♪Us this way♪

484
00:26:24,580 --> 00:26:25,540
♪How I wish♪

485
00:26:25,540 --> 00:26:28,340
♪That you could hear my voice♪

486
00:26:28,580 --> 00:26:33,220
♪And know I won't forget you♪

487
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:37,940
♪Never forget you♪

488
00:26:44,820 --> 00:26:45,860
Fermented sparkling wine.

489
00:26:46,660 --> 00:26:47,500
Zero alcohol.

490
00:26:48,340 --> 00:26:49,300
But these bubbles

491
00:26:49,940 --> 00:26:51,020
still give you a kick.

492
00:26:51,860 --> 00:26:52,180
Cheers.

493
00:26:57,180 --> 00:26:58,300
What are you so happy about?

494
00:26:59,460 --> 00:27:00,620
Did your son come to you?

495
00:27:01,100 --> 00:27:02,340
My son didn't come.

496
00:27:03,180 --> 00:27:04,660
His friend came looking for me.

497
00:27:05,260 --> 00:27:05,860
We chatted

498
00:27:06,180 --> 00:27:07,340
for a long time.

499
00:27:07,780 --> 00:27:09,180
Your son sent him, didn't he?

500
00:27:09,620 --> 00:27:10,420
He won't admit it.

501
00:27:11,140 --> 00:27:12,260
But from what I observed,

502
00:27:12,620 --> 00:27:13,700
it was definitely my son

503
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:15,660
who sent him to spy on me.

504
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:17,140
Don't worry.

505
00:27:17,700 --> 00:27:18,780
I can stand the test.

506
00:27:19,622 --> 00:27:21,020
Did you show him your notebook?

507
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:22,100
Yes, he saw it.

508
00:27:22,860 --> 00:27:24,900
It's been 2,237 days without a drink.

509
00:27:25,300 --> 00:27:26,460
He even took photos.

510
00:27:27,940 --> 00:27:30,340
He'll definitely report back to my son.

511
00:27:31,260 --> 00:27:32,260
I realized

512
00:27:33,140 --> 00:27:34,740
my son is going to come back.

513
00:27:35,940 --> 00:27:37,860
With me turning over a new leaf,

514
00:27:38,060 --> 00:27:39,540
he's bound to forgive me.

515
00:27:39,540 --> 00:27:40,060
He will.

516
00:27:40,060 --> 00:27:40,340
Cheers.

517
00:27:46,820 --> 00:27:47,940
If your son does come back,

518
00:27:48,340 --> 00:27:49,260
what about the shop?

519
00:27:50,140 --> 00:27:52,180
Why would I keep it open?

520
00:27:52,460 --> 00:27:54,020
I'm going to be a healthy old man.

521
00:27:55,100 --> 00:27:56,980
I'll wake up at 5:00 AM,

522
00:27:57,340 --> 00:27:59,260
and go to bed at 9:00 PM.

523
00:28:00,220 --> 00:28:00,660
If my son

524
00:28:00,940 --> 00:28:02,140
has kids,

525
00:28:02,333 --> 00:28:03,580
I'll help him take care of them.

526
00:28:03,900 --> 00:28:04,740
If not,

527
00:28:04,940 --> 00:28:06,020
I'll help him walk the dog.

528
00:28:07,066 --> 00:28:08,580
I'll be waiting for your good news.

529
00:28:10,380 --> 00:28:10,780
Wait.

530
00:28:12,220 --> 00:28:13,700
If I close my shop,

531
00:28:14,060 --> 00:28:15,220
where will you go at night?

532
00:28:16,140 --> 00:28:17,340
No need to worry about me.

533
00:28:17,933 --> 00:28:20,620
There are plenty of people
with bad father-son relationships.

534
00:28:20,900 --> 00:28:22,060
There's another old man

535
00:28:22,060 --> 00:28:23,060
running a shop somewhere,

536
00:28:23,060 --> 00:28:24,300
spending his days in misery.

537
00:28:27,977 --> 00:28:29,200
I shouldn't have worried.

538
00:28:34,540 --> 00:28:35,940
Your young friend is here for you.

539
00:28:46,740 --> 00:28:47,380
It's sent?

540
00:28:49,180 --> 00:28:49,780
Thank you.

541
00:28:49,980 --> 00:28:50,780
Don't mention it.

542
00:28:51,466 --> 00:28:52,540
If you hadn't dozed off,

543
00:28:52,540 --> 00:28:53,740
you would've finished it.

544
00:28:55,777 --> 00:28:57,340
So why did you come looking for me

545
00:28:57,780 --> 00:28:58,740
so late at night?

546
00:29:01,780 --> 00:29:02,380
To help.

547
00:29:08,266 --> 00:29:09,980
I can't write long novels anymore,

548
00:29:10,260 --> 00:29:12,020
but I can still help edit drafts.

549
00:29:17,700 --> 00:29:18,780
Your account got suspended?

550
00:29:20,180 --> 00:29:20,740
For a month.

551
00:29:22,044 --> 00:29:23,020
That's a long time.

552
00:29:23,020 --> 00:29:24,220
What are you going to do now?

553
00:29:26,860 --> 00:29:27,860
I sell classes online.

554
00:29:29,740 --> 00:29:30,620
What kind of classes?

555
00:29:30,740 --> 00:29:31,700
Web novel writing.

556
00:29:32,620 --> 00:29:33,140
Oh my.

557
00:29:33,980 --> 00:29:35,740
You used to hate even doing interviews.

558
00:29:36,100 --> 00:29:37,060
I'm not like you.

559
00:29:37,060 --> 00:29:38,580
I know how to adapt, okay?

560
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:41,660
Give me a break.

561
00:29:42,711 --> 00:29:44,088
Who hooked you up with this?

562
00:29:45,900 --> 00:29:46,780
An old friend.

563
00:29:47,355 --> 00:29:49,580
The so-called phoenix head,
leopard tail, and pig belly.

564
00:29:49,740 --> 00:29:51,380
We start with the phoenix head.

565
00:29:51,660 --> 00:29:52,420
Everyone knows

566
00:29:52,420 --> 00:29:53,340
that readers will read

567
00:29:53,360 --> 00:29:54,100
only three pages.

568
00:29:54,100 --> 00:29:55,860
If they don't find the hook,

569
00:29:55,860 --> 00:29:56,900
they'll just drop it.

570
00:29:57,140 --> 00:29:58,500
Your characters, plot, and setting

571
00:29:58,500 --> 00:30:01,020
have to be spectacular
right out of the gate.

572
00:30:01,100 --> 00:30:02,700
Let's compare two novels.

573
00:30:03,420 --> 00:30:04,860
